<DOC><DOCNO> AP890427-0277 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-27-89 1938EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-PlasticBags     04-27 0230</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Plastic Bags,0240</SECOND><HEAD>Reynolds' New Bags Latest Effort To Insulate Firm From Cyclical Declines</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Reynolds Metals Co. Thursday introduced a lineof plastic storage bags, continuing its strategy of focusing onconsumer products to help insulate the big aluminum maker fromcyclical declines in aluminum markets.   The Richmond, Va.-based company unveiled a 10-item line ofReynolds Sure-Seal reclosable plastic bags at a New York newsconference.   The sandwich, food storage and freezer bags were described asthe most durable ones that will be available in the $500 millionmarket and they have a ``triple track'' closure designed to providea tight seal for freshness, leak resistance and ease of opening andclosing.   Earlier this year, Reynolds expanded its plastic wrap line byintroducing colored versions.   Reynolds has been expanding its consumer products business forseveral years, acquiring in the process Cut-Rite wax paper, Baker'sChoice paper products and Presto products.   ``We have followed that strategy with great care andattention,'' said William O. Bourke, Reynolds chairman and chiefexecutive.   ``These are high-added value, recession-resistant products,'' hesaid in a prepared statement. ``They help insulate our company fromthe ups and downs of a cyclical world aluminum market.''   Reynolds is one of the nation's largest aluminum manufacturers,a precious metals producer and consumer products company. Its mostwidely known consumer product is Reynolds Wrap aluminum foil.</TEXT></DOC>